{
  "info": {
    "name": "dealership-bff — Dealership AI",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "description": "Postman collection for the Dealership BFF.\n\nBase URL: http://localhost:8083 (local dev) or the API Gateway V2 invoke URL (LocalStack).\n\n─── Authentication (PKCE / Session-cookie flow) ───────────────────────\nLogin and registration happen through Keycloak's browser UI — not via API calls.\nPostman cannot drive a browser flow, so the steps are:\n\n  LOGIN:\n  1. Open in browser: {{baseUrl}}/oauth2/authorization/keycloak\n  2. Log in on the Keycloak page (e.g. client-user / client-pass)\n  3. Browser is redirected to localhost:3000 (no frontend — expected error)\n  4. Open browser DevTools → Application → Cookies → localhost:8083 → copy SESSION value\n  5. Paste the value into the 'sessionCookie' collection variable\n\n  REGISTER (new user):\n  1. Open in browser: {{baseUrl}}/oauth2/authorization/keycloak-register\n  2. Fill in the Keycloak registration form (first name, last name, email, password)\n  3. Browser redirects to localhost:3000/register/complete (expected error)\n  4. Copy SESSION cookie from DevTools (same as above) → paste into 'sessionCookie'\n  5. Send the 'Complete registration (business data)' request\n\nAll authenticated requests send the SESSION cookie via Cookie header automatically\nonce you set the {{sessionCookie}} variable."
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:8083",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "BFF base URL. For local dev: http://localhost:8083. For LocalStack: http://api-dealership-ai.elb.localhost.localstack.cloud:8083."
    },
    {
      "key": "sessionCookie",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "SESSION cookie value obtained after completing the PKCE login or registration flow in the browser. See collection description for instructions."
    },
    {
      "key": "carId",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "UUID of a car from the inventory — set manually or from the car-api collection"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Actuator health",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/actuator/health",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["actuator", "health"]
            },
            "description": "Spring Boot Actuator health endpoint. No authentication required."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "[BROWSER] 1a. Initiate login",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/oauth2/authorization/keycloak",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["oauth2", "authorization", "keycloak"]
            },
            "description": "⚠️  OPEN THIS URL IN A BROWSER — do not send from Postman.\n\nStarts the PKCE Authorization Code flow for login. Redirects to the Keycloak login page.\nAfter a successful login, Keycloak redirects back to the BFF which sets the SESSION cookie and redirects to the frontend (localhost:3000).\n\nTo use the session in Postman:\n  1. Open {{baseUrl}}/oauth2/authorization/keycloak in your browser\n  2. Log in (e.g. client-user / client-pass)\n  3. DevTools → Application → Cookies → http://localhost:8083 → copy SESSION value\n  4. Paste into the 'sessionCookie' collection variable"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "[BROWSER] 1b. Initiate registration",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/oauth2/authorization/keycloak-register",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["oauth2", "authorization", "keycloak-register"]
            },
            "description": "⚠️  OPEN THIS URL IN A BROWSER — do not send from Postman.\n\nStarts the PKCE Authorization Code flow for registration. Redirects to the Keycloak registration page (not the login page).\nAfter the user submits the Keycloak form, the BFF sets the SESSION cookie and redirects to localhost:3000/register/complete.\n\nTo continue:\n  1. Open {{baseUrl}}/oauth2/authorization/keycloak-register in your browser\n  2. Fill in the Keycloak registration form\n  3. DevTools → Application → Cookies → http://localhost:8083 → copy SESSION value\n  4. Paste into the 'sessionCookie' collection variable\n  5. Send the 'Complete registration (business data)' request below"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "2. Complete registration (business data)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Cookie", "value": "SESSION={{sessionCookie}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"cpf\": \"529.982.247-25\",\n  \"phone\": \"+55 (11) 91234-5678\",\n  \"cep\": \"01310-100\",\n  \"streetNumber\": \"100\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/register",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "register"]
            },
            "description": "Second step of registration — only needed for NEW users (not on every login).\n\nSends the business data (CPF, phone, address) that Keycloak does not collect.\nThe user identity (name, email, Keycloak ID) is extracted automatically from the SESSION.\n\nRequires: SESSION cookie set after completing the Keycloak registration form (step 1b).\nReturns 201 on success."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Refresh access token",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Cookie", "value": "SESSION={{sessionCookie}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/refresh",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "refresh"]
            },
            "description": "Uses the refresh token stored in the server-side session to obtain a new access token. Returns 401 if the session has expired or the refresh token is invalid."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Logout",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Cookie", "value": "SESSION={{sessionCookie}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/logout",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "logout"]
            },
            "description": "Revokes the Keycloak refresh token and invalidates the server-side session. Returns 204 on success.\nAfter logout, clear the 'sessionCookie' collection variable."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Inventory",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List inventory (no filter)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/inventory?page=0&size=20&sortBy=registrationDate&sortDirection=desc",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "inventory"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "page", "value": "0" },
                { "key": "size", "value": "20" },
                { "key": "sortBy", "value": "registrationDate" },
                { "key": "sortDirection", "value": "desc" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Returns a paginated list of available cars. Public endpoint — no authentication required."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "List inventory (with filters)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/inventory?q=Civic&manufacturer=Honda&category=SEDAN&condition=new&yearMin=2020&yearMax=2025&priceMin=30000&priceMax=80000&sortBy=listedValue&sortDirection=asc&page=0&size=10",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "inventory"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "q", "value": "Civic", "description": "Free-text search term" },
                { "key": "manufacturer", "value": "Honda", "description": "Filter by manufacturer" },
                { "key": "category", "value": "SEDAN", "description": "SUV | SEDAN | SPORT | HATCH | PICKUP" },
                { "key": "condition", "value": "new", "description": "new | used" },
                { "key": "yearMin", "value": "2020", "description": "Minimum manufacturing year" },
                { "key": "yearMax", "value": "2025", "description": "Maximum manufacturing year" },
                { "key": "priceMin", "value": "30000", "description": "Minimum listed value" },
                { "key": "priceMax", "value": "80000", "description": "Maximum listed value" },
                { "key": "sortBy", "value": "listedValue", "description": "Field to sort by" },
                { "key": "sortDirection", "value": "asc", "description": "asc | desc" },
                { "key": "page", "value": "0" },
                { "key": "size", "value": "10" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "List inventory using all available filters. Public endpoint."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get car by ID",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/inventory/{{carId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "inventory", "{{carId}}"]
            },
            "description": "Retrieves a single car from the inventory by UUID. Public endpoint. Set {{carId}} from the car-api collection or the list response."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Purchases",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Initiate a purchase",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Cookie", "value": "SESSION={{sessionCookie}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"carId\": \"{{carId}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/purchases",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "purchases"]
            },
            "description": "Initiates a car purchase for the authenticated client. The BFF orchestrates calls to client-api, car-api and sales-api. Requires ROLE_CLIENT session.\n\nSet {{carId}} from the inventory listing first. Returns 201 with the purchase details on success."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get purchase history",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Cookie", "value": "SESSION={{sessionCookie}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/purchases?page=0&size=20",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "purchases"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "page", "value": "0" },
                { "key": "size", "value": "20" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Returns the purchase history for the authenticated client. Requires ROLE_CLIENT session."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get purchase history (date range)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Cookie", "value": "SESSION={{sessionCookie}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/purchases?page=0&size=20&from=2024-01-01T00:00:00Z&to=2024-12-31T23:59:59Z",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "purchases"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "page", "value": "0" },
                { "key": "size", "value": "20" },
                { "key": "from", "value": "2024-01-01T00:00:00Z", "description": "ISO-8601 instant" },
                { "key": "to", "value": "2024-12-31T23:59:59Z", "description": "ISO-8601 instant" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Returns purchase history filtered by date range. Requires ROLE_CLIENT session."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Profile",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get my profile",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Cookie", "value": "SESSION={{sessionCookie}}" }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/profile",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "profile"]
            },
            "description": "Returns the profile of the authenticated user, aggregating data from client-api. Requires ROLE_CLIENT session."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Update my profile",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Cookie", "value": "SESSION={{sessionCookie}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"firstName\": \"João Carlos\",\n  \"lastName\": \"Silva\",\n  \"phone\": \"+55 (11) 99876-5432\",\n  \"cep\": \"04538-133\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/profile",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "profile"]
            },
            "description": "Updates the authenticated user's profile. Delegates to client-api. Requires ROLE_CLIENT session. All fields are optional — at least one must be provided."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Validation Errors (negative tests)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "[400] Register — invalid CPF",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Cookie", "value": "SESSION={{sessionCookie}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"cpf\": \"00000000000\",\n  \"phone\": \"+55 (11) 91234-5678\",\n  \"cep\": \"01310-100\",\n  \"streetNumber\": \"100\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/register",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "register"]
            },
            "description": "Should return 400 VALIDATION_ERROR — CPF is arithmetically invalid."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "[401] Register — no session",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"cpf\": \"529.982.247-25\",\n  \"phone\": \"+55 (11) 91234-5678\",\n  \"cep\": \"01310-100\",\n  \"streetNumber\": \"100\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/register",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "register"]
            },
            "description": "Should return 401 — the register endpoint requires an authenticated session."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "[400] Purchase — missing carId",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Cookie", "value": "SESSION={{sessionCookie}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/purchases",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "purchases"]
            },
            "description": "Should return 400 — carId is required."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "[401] Purchase — no session",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"carId\": \"{{carId}}\"\n}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/purchases",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "purchases"]
            },
            "description": "Should return 401 — no SESSION cookie provided."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "[404] Get non-existent car from inventory",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/inventory/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "inventory", "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000"]
            },
            "description": "Should return 404 — car does not exist in the inventory."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "[401] Refresh — no session",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/refresh",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "refresh"]
            },
            "description": "Call without a SESSION cookie. Should return 401."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
